{
  "stem": "24814.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had a long night march through Luxembourg, up the Moselle, through the burning city of Trier, and over the pontoon bridge and into Germany.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we were in a wild, cavalry, shoot-them-up campaign that lasted about 10 days.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the rear.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Three Army divisions abreast, we slammed into the rear of a whole German Army Group, who were facing south.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they looked over their shoulders and here we came.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was mad.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At One point, we didn't sleep for three days and three nights, once, I remember.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You'd be running through German artillery from the rear with horses galloping through the flames.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we finally met the Seventh Army coming up at the city of Speyer on the Rhine.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were the lead division in the whole Third Army attack in the Sauer Basin.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We led the way to the Rhine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And because we weren't Third Army, Georgie Patton wouldn't release our division identity.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the newspapers knew perfectly well who we were, the correspondents, the called us the mystery division.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mystery division leads Patton's army to the Rhine, that was us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we rested there a little bit, and went back toward Seventh Army, crossed under smokescreen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the dead of night, crossed the Rhine at Mannheim.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And attacked straight east into the Odenwald, the mountains that are a continuation north of the Schwarzwald-- the Black Forest.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we really went-- the US Army official histories describe the 12th Army.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They said, they went through the tangles of the Odenwald like a bobcat through-- like a scalded cat through a thicket.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We really moved in little task forces.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's when I had a lot to do with Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I met them everywhere.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I talked to them everywhere, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
